      "comment_id" : 90317220,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This answer doesn&#39;t make a whole lot of sense. <code>Collections.copy</code> is not at all an alternative to <code>new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(source)</code>. What <code>Collections.copy</code> actually does is assume that <code>destination.size()</code> is at least as big as <code>source.size()</code>, and then copy the range index-by-index using the <code>set(int,E)</code> method. The method doesn&#39;t <i>add</i> new elements to the destination. <a href=\"http://hg.openjdk.java.net/jdk8/jdk8/jdk/file/687fd7c7986d/src/share/classes/java/util/Collections.java#l596\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Refer to the source code if it&#39;s not clear enough from the Javadoc.</a>"
    }, {
