    "body" : "<p>Yes <code>l1</code> and <code>l2</code> will point to the same reference, same object.</p>\n\n<p>If you want to create a new ArrayList based on the other ArrayList you do this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; l1 = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\nl1.add(\"Hello\");\nl1.add(\"World\");\nList&lt;String&gt; l2 = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;(l1); //A new arrayList.\nl2.add(\"Everybody\");\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The result will be <code>l1</code> will still have 2 elements and <code>l2</code> will have 3 elements.</p>\n"
