  "title" : "Java ArrayList copy",
  "body" : "<p>I have an <code>ArrayList</code> <code>l1</code> of size 10. I assign <code>l1</code> to new list reference type <code>l2</code>. Will <code>l1</code> and <code>l2</code> point to same <code>ArrayList</code> object? Or is a copy of the <code>ArrayList</code> object assigned to <code>l2</code>?</p>\n\n<p>When using the <code>l2</code> reference, if I update the list object, it reflects the changes in the <code>l1</code> reference type also.</p>\n\n<p>For example: </p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;Integer&gt; l1 = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;();\nfor (int i = 1; i &lt;= 10; i++) {\n    l1.add(i);\n}\n\nList l2 = l1;\nl2.clear();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Is there no other way to assign a copy of a list object to a new reference variable, apart from creating 2 list objects, and doing copy on collections from old to new?</p>\n"
}